            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(ST) In nomine Domini. Anno ab incarnacione domini nostri Iesu Christi
                        nongentesimo nonagesimo sesto, mense aprilis, indicione nona. [Petimus nos
                            <persName ref="#people/4694" key="#Agricultural_workers #parentOf"
                            >Giseverga</persName> relicta <persName><name ref="Ursus"
                            >Ursoni</name></persName> et] <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers #childOf"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#parentOf">mat(re) </rs>et <rs key="#childOf">filio</rs> de <rs
                            key="#Vici">vico</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Vici">Calcinate</placeName> a te] <persName key="#Priests"
                                ><name ref="Ingo">Ingo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et prepositus de or[d]ine canonice
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/189"><rs key="#Churches">Sancti
                                Al[lexan]dri</rs></orgName> ut nobis qui supra petitori dare hac
                        prestare iubeatis sicuti nobis de presente prestitisti ad abendum, tenendum
                        seu censum reddendum livellando nomine usque ad annos <rs
                            key="#Rent_in_money">viginti et nove expletos,</rs> id est quarta
                        portione de una <rs key="#Landed_possessions">sorte</rs> de <geogName
                            ref="#estates/4232" key="#Petiae">Sussiaco</geogName> iuris eglesie
                        canonice Sancti Allexandri, que ante os dies ipsa quarta portione rec[ta et]
                        laborata fuit per Ursonem et Petronem <rs key="#siblingOf">germanis</rs>,
                        uti amodo promittimus nos peditori cum nostri eredes suprascripta terra
                        abere, tenere [,..] et seminare, ut aput nos meliorentur, nam non
                        depeiorentur et persolvamus vobis exinde singulis annis usque termino
                        constituto per omne festivitate sancti Laurenti <rs key="#Rent_in_kind"><rs
                                key="#Cereals">granum</rs> grauso sestaria septe et mina una,</rs>
                        per festivitate sancti Martini grano minuto sestaria septe et mina una,
                        argenti denarios numeros quinque, pro tempore vendemie <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vinum</rs> medietatem, datum et consignatum sit censum ipsum per nos
                        ipsos petitores aut per nostros eredes vel per nostro <rs key="#Missus"
                            >misso</rs> tibi Ingoni presbitero aut ad vestros successoribus vel ad
                        vestro miso in casa abitacionis vestre in vestra <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitate</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/10" key="#Cities">Bergamo</placeName>; alia
                        superinposita non inponatur. Pena vero inter nos posuerimus ut quis ex nobis
                        aut eredes vel successores nostros se de hac conveniencia libelli removere
                        quesierint et non permanserint in ea omnia, qualiter superius legitur, tunc
                        pars illa que hoc non conservaverit componat ad partem fidem servantis<rs
                            key="#Penalty"> argenti denarios bonos solidos viginti</rs> et post pena
                        composita hunc libellum in suo maneat robore; quia sic inter nobis convenit.
                        Actum [...]m. [(SC) Ingo presbiter et prepositus] a me facta subscripsi.
                        [(SC) <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Teudualdus"
                            >Teutaldus</name></persName> presbiter subscripsi]. [(SC) <persName
                            key="#Priests"><name ref="Leo">Leo</name></persName>] presbiter et
                        primicerius rogatus supscripsi. (SC) <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Teudualdus">Petrus</name></persName> presbiter subscripsi. (SC)
                            <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Adalbertus"
                            >Adelbertus</name></persName> presbiter subscripsi. (SC) <persName
                            key="#Deacons"><name ref="Umbertus">Umbertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs> subscripsi. (SC) <persName key="#Priests"
                                ><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> presbiter subscripsi.
                        (S) <persName key="#Deacons"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName>
                        diaconus supscripsi. [(SC)] <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannes</name></persName> subscripsi. Signum +++ manibus <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Dachipertus">Dagiberti</name></persName> qui
                        et [,..], <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohanne</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Tunipertus">Tuniberti</name></persName> pater et filius, isti
                        de civitate Bergamo, testes. (ST) <persName key="#Notary"><name
                                ref="Lazarus">Lazarus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> sacri palacii scripsi, post tradita complevi
                        et dedi.</ab>
